-- Serbian Copper Miner Plans 30% Increase in Copper Output in 2013
-- B y   G o r d a n a   F i l i p o v i c
-- 2012-12-24T09:34:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-24/serbian-copper-miner-plans-30-increase-in-copper-output-in-2013.html
RTB Bor,  Serbia ’s sole copper
producer, plans to increase output by about 30 percent and post
$7.27 million in net income next year.  The state-run company plans to produce 42,230 tons of
copper cathodes as well as 917 kilograms of gold and 5.2 tons of
silver next year, the company said in an e-mailed statement
today. It gave no figures for this year’s gold and silver output
or net income.  Bor also plans to invest $330 million next year, including
a new smelter, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gordana Filipovic in Belgrade at 
 gfilipovic@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  